name: Cmodel Upgrade! Stable diffusion version 2
description:
Like with all V2 models you need to YAML to use Make sure you download it in the training data

Here's my V2 model, it's my favorite model to date! So much detail! This model is mostly based on the artist cromwaits. "cmodel" is a trigger word but isn't needed.


Prompt examples and tips:

prompt: digital illustration, cinematic lighting, smooth, hyper-realistic, mfs shot, best quality, high detail, masterpiece, high quality, Russian winter streetwear, (midriff:1.3), bloom, film grain, detailed eyes, beautiful face, (skinny:1.2), (young female:1.3), city background


Negative prompt: white background, B&W, ( fangs, lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, fangs:1.3),( Deformed, blurry,, disfigured, poorly drawn face, mutation, mutated, extra limb, ugly, poorly drawn hands, missing limb, blurry, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, malformed hands, blur, out of focus, long neck, long body, mutated hands and fingers, text, out of frame:1.3) Additionally, this model is friendly hypernets, and Clip skipping! For low-step samplers the CFG's 4 & 7 work really well.

Enjoy!


User info:

Make sure to join my patreon to support and get the latest models early!

https://www.patreon.com/Rahmel

Additionally, if you don't like patreon and would like to support here is a donation link

https://cash.app/$RahmelJackson

I definitely could need the support this December, thank you so, so much if you can help out.

modelVersions.name: Safetensor Version
modelVersions.description:
No pickles, This safetensor version is better than CKPT. Works exactly the same and safer.

Like with all V2 models you need to also download this Yaml file inorder to use the model, simply just put the YAML file in the same place as the model, and it will load when you run the model

I put the YAML file in the Training Data Section, so you can download it

Make sure you download it or you will get an error.
